entries.femaleVariant: Whatever happened to Thompson?
[Stand] Never told me all that about Alt. Nothing close.
[Stand] Wow, you were a real douchebag.
Never even told me half that about Alt.
Wow. Were you going for Douchebag of the Year?
entries.maleVariant: Wow. Were you going for Dickwipe of the Year?

entries.femaleVariant: And here I was afraid you'd try to cheer me up.
The fuck you going on about?!
Alt.
Never mind. You sure glossed over Alt's story earlier.
Well, what's not to like, scout, hm?
You treated Alt like shit.
Never gave me the whole story about Alt. But never mind.
The way you treated Alt.
You – an ungrateful, self-centered bastard.
That you were an ungrateful, self-centered prick – that's what.
An asshole to everybody – Thompson, Rogue, Alt…
And I'm wondering why. I mean, you told her you two were nothing. You told you cared about her as far as the end of your cock.
entries.maleVariant: And I'm wondering why. I mean, you told her you two were nothin'. You told you cared about her as far as the end of your cock.

entries.femaleVariant: Never mind. But you sure glossed over Alt earlier.
Alt. You always treat her like shit?
Didn't you fucking hear what she said to me?
Coulda just left, but no, had to break my balls first.
Really? Any examples...?
I dunno – that you were a couple, that she wrote Soulkiller, that she's dead?
How the hell's she supposed to help us now? As a ghost?
She's not dead. Managed to escape.
I saw the body.
Alt fled. Into the Net.
When'd you find that out?
Bullshit.
When'd you find out?
When she made contact, a little later.
You're pushin' bullshit. Heard more than my share o' tales about runners who ran off to Never-Never Netland.
entries.maleVariant: You're pushin' bullshit. Heard more than my share of tales 'bout runners who ran off to Never-Never Netland.

entries.femaleVariant: NetWatch could've tracked Alt down by now.
And Rogue went with you. Again.
Where nobody can touch her.
And Brigitte's primed to go there, break through. Just to contact Alt, talk to her.
Ka-ching.
Too much for our little pro?
Ever occur to you she might've been right?
Whatever. Maybe you deserved each other.
It ever occur to you she might've been right?
Taking her side? What is this – strength in unity, strength in numbers?
Oh, haven't changed a bit.
What's that supposed to mean?
Looking at it now, with twenty-twenty hindsight, nothing occurs to you?
entries.maleVariant: Lookin' at it now, with twenty-twenty hindsight, nothin' occurs to you?

entries.femaleVariant: No. But this is a bit of a deja vu. You're as bad as she was. Can't understand why you can't just fuckin' drop it.
Cause you're planning a reunion. You wanna ask Alt for help.
And you're no solo act, Johnny.
How's Alt supposed to help us? I saw her die.
So how the hell you expect Alt to help us? I saw her get decommed.
Just tryin' to wrap my head around it. You went to rescue her 'cause you actually cared about her?
Felt you had unfinished biz?
Or was it just another excuse to go at Arasaka?
Guess.
What? Why?
Could've told me about Alt earlier.
She didn't die. She got out, escaped.
Well, looked to me like…
She fled into the Net.
This one time she wanted me to just let it go.
Could've told me earlier, about Alt.
No, it hasn't. She was manipulative, had an agenda.
Thought that was more your style?
What the hell for? I didn't know how to find 'er, neither did you.
Woulda made things just a little easier, knowing who we were lookin' for.
Just never thought you'd be the next to tell me one.
Don't need you to believe me long as you do exactly what I say.
And Rogue went with you. Again.
Thompson – what happened to 'im?
Dunno. Never worked together again.
Maybe 'cause you whooped his ass to make yourself feel better.
Guy was a vulture. Out to use Alt from the start. When Arasaka flatlined 'er, man, for him that was sprinkles... with a cherry on top.
Fuck, he woulda killed 'er himself if they hadn't. Just for his cockrot story.
Well? Spit it out 'fore you burst.
I paid 'er well.
Said it yourself, she was the best. Had 'er pick of contracts.
entries.maleVariant: Said it yourself – she was the best. Had 'er pick of contracts.

entries.femaleVariant: But for some strange-ass reason, she took a job from a rocker with a death wish. A rocker forever getting his ass beat by Arasaka.
Different times, kid. Back then, mercs didn't normally sell out to corps.
All ya had to do was yell "Let's fuck up Arasaka!" and every last one of 'em jizzed their pants. Rogue included.
Voodoo Boys think they know where she is – beyond the Blackwall.
The recording – Thompson ever release it?
The recording – what'd Thompson do with it? It ever get released?
Fuck no.
Prove it.
Prove it, prove that she escaped . How'd that even be possible?
Don't know. I'm not a hotshot deckslinger.
Alt's control of Soulkiller was complete.
Even after the 'Saka runners caged her and forced her to rewrite the code.
She found a way, slipped through their grubby corpo fingers.
Voodoo Boys believe Alt's beyond the Blackwall.
What? Why?
So... what did you do?
Got my hands on two thermonuclear charges.
Then headed back to Arasaka Tower.
What'd you do?
How d'you know Alt's still around? It's been a half century. Which you've spent cloistered in Mikoshi.
NetWatch coulda hunted her down years ago.
Oh, they tried, believe me. But their tiny corporate brains can't handle a free AI that knows how people think.
They were busy looking for her in the Crystal Palace. While she was building the Ghost City for Kang Tao.
Don't you fuckin' mention Alt. Shit, you must've been watching some other flick! I took down Arasaka-fuckin'-Tower for her!
Just trying to understand.
Ugh. Whatever. Maybe you two deserved each other.
entries.maleVariant: Whatever. Maybe you two deserved each other.

entries.femaleVariant: It was a... passionate affair, that's clear. Shouldn't pry beyond that.
Good. Don't.
And? What'd she say?
And she told me not to come lookin' for her.
That she was a captive in the Arasaka subnet. But they couldn't hurt her.
'Cause enough people had died for nothing already.
[Return to BBS]
